        public <T extends Entity<T>> T create(Class<T> cls,
                             CreationEvent<T> event)
        Returns a new instance of type T using the given CreationEvent. This is a synchronous creation using a newly created then closed EntityManager for persisting the entity. If you need finer grained control of commits then open your own entity manager and do the the persist yourself.
